eamwork), egocentric (teamwork), not willing to further education (professional development). Overall strong reliability and calm, but teamwork communication issues.\n\nD: Responds adequately to unexpected (calm), concentration, problem solving, responsibility (reliability), but hot temper (teamwork), know-it-all (teamwork), weak leadership. No explicit reliability but responsibility suggests reliability. No explicit stress handling.\n\nNow weigh: For long-distance flights, reliability and calm under pressure are crucial, plus teamwork/communication. B has stress handling but poor teamwork. C has reliability and calm, but communication difficulty. D has responsibility but hot temper. A has leadership but unknown stress handling.\n\nThus the best candidate might be C because reliability and calm are top, and positive crew atmosphere offsets some communication difficulty. However egocentric and unwillingness to further education could be issues for long-term development. B's teamwork issues may be more severe for safety. A's unknown stress handling is a risk.\n\nThus I might lean toward Candidate C as provisional preference, but note uncertainty due to communication and professional development.\n\nWe should also note that we lack info on A's reliability and stress handling, and B's teamwork and reliability beyond conscientiousness. So we could ask others for those.\n\nThus produce public message: provisional preference Candidate C, with reasoning, mention alternatives B and A, tradeoffs, uncertainties, what would change vote (e.g., evidence of strong teamwork for B, or reliability for A, or that C's communication issues cause crew conflict). Provide metadata vote."}
